{"lemma":"سَلِيم","slug":"سَلِيم","root":"س.ل.م","root_slug":"س-ل-م","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ل-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سَلِيم","root":"سلم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","name"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20548"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%85"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"safe, secure"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"healthy"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"free (from, with مِن (min))"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a male given name, Saleem"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"فَعِيل (faʕīl)-type stative-verb derived from the active participle from the verb سَلِمَ (salima, “to be safe”)."},"ipa":["/sa.liːm/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20548","headword_ar":"سَلِيمٌ","root":"slm","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAlimN","text_ar":"سَالِمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) which means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Safe, secure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from evils of any kind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, Msb, TA;) applied to a man: (M:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sulamaA='u","text_ar":"سُلَمَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K, TA;) in some copies of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salomaY","text_ar":"سَلْمَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaroHaY","text_ar":"جَرْحَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jariyHN","text_ar":"جَرِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) [but this is probably its pl. only when it is used in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jariyHN","text_ar":"جَرِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the like, as seems to be the case from what follows.] Also, (M,) applied to a"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1416},{"kind":"text","text":"heart: (S, M:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biqalobK saliymK","text_ar":"بِقَلْبٍ سَلِيمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur xxvi. 89, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"With a heart free from unbelief:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"divested of corruptness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unsoundness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA:) in the Kur xxxvii. 82, some say that it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a grieving,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sorrowful, heart;"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saliymN","text_ar":"سَلِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense here next following. (Bd.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ladiygN","text_ar":"لَدِيغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Bitten by a serpent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, M, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAmN","text_ar":"سَلَامٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masoluwmN","text_ar":"مَسْلُومٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) app., (S,) as implying a good omen, of safety; (S, M;) or because the person is left ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musolamN","text_ar":"مُسْلَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") to that [bane] which is in him: (IAar, S, * M:) and sometimes it is metaphorically used as meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wounded:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wounded, at the point of death,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) as some say: (M:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salomaY","text_ar":"سَلْمَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, and Ham p. 214.)       -A2-  Also, (M, K,) of a horse, (M,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part, of the hoof, that is between the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oEar","text_ar":"اَشْعَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremity of the skin, next the hoof"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (M, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is between the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amoEar","text_ar":"اَمْعَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.], (K,) but the former is the right, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the interior of the hoof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","Msb","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}